SIMPLE: waterwork
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waterwork
<hw>Wa"ter*work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>Painting executed in size or distemper, on
canvas or walls, -- formerly, frequently taking the place of
tapestry.</def> <rj><au>Shak. Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An hydraulic apparatus, or a system of works or
fixtures, by which a supply of water is furnished for useful or
ornamental purposes, including dams, sluices, pumps, aqueducts,
distributing pipes, fountains, etc.; -- used chiefly in the
plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- Water works. The plant and equipment used to purify water for
drinking and other purposes, and to supply it to the mains of a town.
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterworn</ent>⟦br⟧
